<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7170] [0.94 branch] Allow HConnectionImplementation to reconnect to master multiple times</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7170</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5058&quot; title=&quot;Allow HBaseAdmin to use an existing connection&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5058&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5058&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; retained the old behavior of managed HConnections not retrying their connection to master b/c of the &quot;masterChecked&quot; variable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This behavior isn&apos;t great though, because you can get in the following situation:&lt;br/&gt;
1) Connect to master using HBaseAdmin&lt;br/&gt;
2) Master goes down&lt;br/&gt;
3) New master takes over&lt;br/&gt;
4) The HBaseAdmin object is now useless&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The client needs to create a new HBaseAdmin in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12616329">HBASE-7170</key>
            <summary>[0.94 branch] Allow HConnectionImplementation to reconnect to master multiple times</summary>
